There's a data race here due to lack of synchronization between these two variables. It's possible for a thread to observe hashComputed == false and hashCode being set to 0.
The only safe way to do this is:
int hash = hashCode;
if (hash == 0) {
    hash = Objects.hash(...);
    hashCode = hash
}

return hash;

Note that this relies on the atomicity semantics for unsynchronized access to int fields.

